There was a smaller yarding of 138 trade and export cattle at Powranna on Thursday with not as many secondary yearlings as last week.
The market was generally similar with yearling steers making 248c to 276 and heifers 230c to 266c.
Grown steers and bullocks made 250c to 282c. The was a similar number of 50 cows and market was fully firm with heavy pens making 220c to 250c and leaner 130c to 190c/kg liveweight.

Market Reporter Richard Bailey
